13. lene tormentum. The meaning seems to be settled by the parallel Epp. 1. 5. 19 ‘ Fecundi calices quem non fecere disertum?’ As the rack makes the unwilling witness speak freely, so wine makes the wit which is usually stiff and taciturn become free and talkative, and yet love the torture which is thus applied to it.
